			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Rapidly growing Ed Tech company seeks Head of Marketing</strong></p>
<p>
<strong><u>Company Description</u></strong><br />
Voxy is a NYC-based company that is using mobile/web applications and sophisticated personalization technology to disrupt the $80B market for language education.&nbsp; Since launch in 2010 as a TechCrunch Disrupt finalist, Voxy has grown to over 2M users, tens of thousands of paying customers, and has the #1 rated education app in Brazil, Mexico, and dozens of other countries around the world.&nbsp; Voxy is backed by leading education investors, and has been recognized as a pioneer by The New York Times, CNN Money, Fast Company, Mashable, Univision, Veja (Brazil), Venturebeat, and others.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">
<em>Recognized by Business Insider:</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">
<strong><a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/10-of-the-best-us-tech-companies-to-work-for-in-2012-2012-3#ixzz29ZXEQUzg">The 10 Best US Tech Companies To Work For In 2012</a></strong></p>
<p>
<u><strong>Role Description</strong></u><br />
We are looking for an aggressive and talented online marketing superstar to lead customer acquisition, retention, and monetization for our rapidly growing global subscription business.&nbsp; The ideal candidate will be entrepreneurial, results-oriented, and love new challenges.&nbsp; We are serious about changing global education, and we are marketing a ground-breaking learning product across multiple platforms in developing markets all over the world.&nbsp; You will be obsessed with winning and enjoy the quantitative, results-oriented nature of online marketing, but also know how to build a team and work in a highly collaborative environment.&nbsp; While the role also will manage brand, PR and other marketing functions, there is a <strong>heavy emphasis on performance marketing to drive profitable conversions.</strong></p>
<p>
<br />
This role reports directly to the CEO and has board-level responsibility, yet will also need to be in the trenches, building a team, and creatively solving problems.&nbsp; A hybrid CRO / &ldquo;growth hacker&rdquo;.</p>
<p>
<u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li>
As part of the 6-person management team, provide senior leadership for the entire revenue function of the company</li>
<li>
Grow ROI-driven marketing spend from current level ($50k / month) to $1M / month</li>
<li>
Develop, implement and manage the company&rsquo;s mobile &amp; web paid customer acquisition strategy; including SEO/SEM, display, email, affiliate and social</li>
<li>
Manage, mentor, and train a team of 2 junior marketers to continually improve ROI of marketing spend (LTV/CPA); manage ad networks, agencies, and other partners</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Demonstrated track record in user acquisition, engagement, retention and monetization for online service (5-10 years experience); management of marketing budgets of $1M+</strong></li>
<li>
Love of data; familiar with the metrics, analytics, and statistics of quantitative marketing</li>
<li>
Deep understanding of cohort analysis and the psychology that drives online engagement and purchases; understand funnels, customer segmentation, lead scoring, etc.</li>
<li>
Experience in online education a huge plus</li>
<li>
Familiarity with international online marketing (Brazil, LatAm, Asia) a huge plus</li>
</ul>
<p>
