<strong>Position Description</strong></p>
<p>
In this hybrid role you will have both general project management responsibilities as well work closely with the engineering team in a scrum master capacity. You will manage the task calendar for our engineering, product and design teams to help them work together more efficiently and perform at the highest levels. Your primary responsibility will be to drive integrated team efforts that will result in successful execution of project initiatives, and to encourage teams to follow the Agile framework. Additional responsibilities will vary day-to-day and include educating and training team members to support a continuous and transparent process improvement philosophy.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>A. Project Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Collaborate with Product and Engineering teams to define the detailed project deliverables</li>
<li>
Develop project plans, goals, and work within guided budget plans; identify resources needed, develop schedules and methods for measuring results</li>
<li>
Ensure that each project work breakdown structure is clarified, prioritized and assigned to the appropriate team member</li>
<li>
Create, maintain and enforce project timelines, milestones and deliverables across all channels to ensure on-time completion</li>
<li>
Oversee the preparation and dissemination of project communications including escalation of project issues and risks (as appropriate)</li>
<li>
Recommend and oversee process re-engineering as applicable</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>B. Scrum Master</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Run sprint planning, as well as release planning and sprint reviews for engineering team</li>
<li>
Coach team on agile practices and encourage adoption via retros, scrums, sprint planning</li>
<li>
Run daily standup meetings, understand &amp; remove obstacles</li>
<li>
Help identify and mitigate risks</li>
<li>
Own the metrics for the engineering team; utilize data to effectively communicate progress and opportunities for improvement with stakeholders and other team members</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong><br />
The ideal candidate is entrepreneurial, results-oriented, and loves new challenges. We are serious about changing global education with our ground-breaking learning product, and surround ourselves with team members who bring this same passion to their work every day as well.</p>
<p>
In addition to passion, energy and enthusiasm for the work that we do, you will also have:</p>
<ul>
<li>
3+ years project management experience in a technology environment</li>
<li>
Bachelor&#39;s degree in Information Systems, Engineering or related field</li>
<li>
Knowledge and experience in cross-functional project management methods and techniques, preferably with startup experience</li>
<li>
Thorough understanding of Agile software development life cycles</li>
<li>
Deep understanding of scrum and other related methodologies that can be leveraged to provide value to a team</li>
<li>
Experience using case and code tracking tools such as Jira</li>
<li>
Demonstrated ability to facilitate and run great, effective meetings</li>
<li>
Strong verbal and written communication skills</li>
<li>
Ability to influence and lead, as well as delegate; facilitator of team work; effectively manages conflict; adaptable, able to keep cool in high-pressure situations</li>
<li>
Qualification in project management a plus;&nbsp; knowledge of both theoretical and practical aspects of project management including tools and processes</li>
</ul>
